title: [Bloodriven Village, Gloam Pike]
description: This section of road is almost entirely hard-packed dirt, although pits the size of small stones hold their shape here and there.  A nondescript building stands on the eastern side, its front porch leaning to one side, while an unstable pyramid of cobblestones stands adjacent.

This section of road is almost entirely hard-packed dirt, the surface covered in various clumps of snow left between deep footprints leading to and away from the area.  A nondescript building stands on the eastern side, its front porch decorated by fragrant wreaths, while an unstable pyramid of cobblestones stands adjacent.
